{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "0beed1a5-a2f9-41a1-bc0b-8c7325d7e04c",
    "name": "Tamkin",
    "description": "This Postman collection is the central API reference for the Tamkin platform. It covers all endpoints for authentication, campaign management, donation payments, and media reels.\n\nThe collection is structured by feature module to reflect the backend architecture, making it easy for frontend developers to integrate.\n\nDesigned for:\n- Client application integration\n- API testing and payload validation\n- QA and automated test pipelines",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "_exporter_id": "40056651"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "0.System",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}",
              "host": [
                "{{BASE_URL}}"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Checks that the server is running and reachable.\n\n**Expected User Data**\nNone"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Get CSRF Token",
          "request": {
            "auth": {
              "type": "noauth"
            },
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/csrf-token",
              "host": [
                "{{BASE_URL}}"
              ],
              "path": [
                "csrf-token"
              ]
            },
            "description": "Generates and returns a CSRF token. The token is also set as a cookie (`x-csrf-token`) in the response.\n\nCall this endpoint first before making any state-changing requests (POST, PUT, DELETE, PATCH). Extract the `token` from the response body and the `x-csrf-token` cookie, then include both in subsequent requests:\n- Header: `x-csrf-token: <token_value>`\n- Cookie: `x-csrf-token=<cookie_value>` (automatically handled by browsers/Postman)\n\n**Expected User Data**\nNone – Public endpoint, no authentication required.\n\n**Response**\n`token` (string) – The CSRF token to use in the `x-csrf-token` header for subsequent requests."
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "System-level utility endpoints for verifying server health and connectivity."
    },
    {
      "name": "Auth",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Login & Session Management",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Login with Google",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "x-csrf-token",
                    "value": "{{CSRF_TOKEN}}",
                    "description": "CSRF protection token",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n    \"id_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJSUzI1NiIsImtpZCI6...\"\n}",
                  "options": {
                    "raw": {
                      "language": "json"
                    }
                  }
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/google",
                  "host": [
                    "{{BASE_URL}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "auth",
                    "google"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Authenticates or registers a user via a Google ID token. Sets session cookies on success. Returns a `status` field indicating whether the user was logged in or newly registered.\n\n**Expected User Data**\n`id_token` (string) – Required, Google OAuth2 ID token obtained from the client"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Register",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "x-csrf-token",
                    "value": "{{CSRF_TOKEN}}",
                    "description": "CSRF protection token",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n    \"fullName\": \"Ahmad Al-Masri\",\n    \"email\": \"ahmad@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"StrongPass@123\",\n    \"confirmPassword\": \"StrongPass@123\",\n    \"nationality\": \"Palestinian\"\n}",
                  "options": {
                    "raw": {
                      "language": "json"
                    }
                  }
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/register",
                  "host": [
                    "{{BASE_URL}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "auth",
                    "register"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Creates a new user account. Sets session cookies on success.\n\n**Expected User Data**\n`fullName` (string) – Required, full name of the user\n`email` (string) – Required, valid email address\n`password` (string) – Required, strong password\n`confirmPassword` (string) – Required, must exactly match `password`\n`nationality` (string) – Required, user's nationality"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Login",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "x-csrf-token",
                    "value": "{{CSRF_TOKEN}}",
                    "description": "CSRF protection token",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n    \"email\": \"ahmad@example.com\",\n    \"password\": \"StrongPass@123\"\n}",
                  "options": {
                    "raw": {
                      "language": "json"
                    }
                  }
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/login",
                  "host": [
                    "{{BASE_URL}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "auth",
                    "login"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Authenticates an existing user with email and password. Sets session cookies on success.\n\n**Expected User Data**\n`email` (string) – Required, registered email address\n`password` (string) – Required, account password"
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Logout",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "x-csrf-token",
                    "value": "{{CSRF_TOKEN}}",
                    "description": "CSRF protection token",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/logout",
                  "host": [
                    "{{BASE_URL}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "auth",
                    "logout"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Clears session cookies and terminates the active session.\n\n**Expected User Data**\nNone – Relies on the session cookie sent by the browser."
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ],
          "description": "Handles user authentication, session creation, and session termination. Covers standard email/password login, Google OAuth, registration, and logout."
        },
        {
          "name": "Email Verification",
          "item": [
            {
              "name": "Request Confirm Email",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "x-csrf-token",
                    "value": "{{CSRF_TOKEN}}",
                    "description": "CSRF protection token",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/request-confirm-email",
                  "host": [
                    "{{BASE_URL}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "auth",
                    "request-confirm-email"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Sends an OTP code to the authenticated user's email to begin the email verification flow. Requires an active session.\n\n**Expected User Data**\nNone – The authenticated user is identified from the session cookie."
              },
              "response": []
            },
            {
              "name": "Confirm Email",
              "request": {
                "method": "POST",
                "header": [
                  {
                    "key": "x-csrf-token",
                    "value": "{{CSRF_TOKEN}}",
                    "description": "CSRF protection token",
                    "type": "text"
                  }
                ],
                "body": {
                  "mode": "raw",
                  "raw": "{\n    \"code\": \"A3F9B2\"\n}",
                  "options": {
                    "raw": {
                      "language": "json"
                    }
                  }
                },
                "url": {
                  "raw": "{{BASE_URL}}/auth/confirm-email",
                  "host": [
                    "{{BASE_URL}}"
                  ],
                  "path": [
                    "auth",
                    "confirm-email"
                  ]
                },
                "description": "Verifies the user's email using the OTP received from `/auth/request-confirm-email`. Requires an active session.\n\n**Expected User Data**\n`code` (string) – Required, the OTP code sent to the user's email"
              },
              "response": []
            }
          ],
          "description": "Handles the two-step email verification flow. First request an OTP, then submit it to confirm ownership of the registered email address."
        }
      ],
      "description": "The Auth module manages the full user authentication lifecycle — registration, login, Google OAuth, session management, and email verification."
    },
    {
      "name": "Campaign",
